# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in to use the DeepSeek backend.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The default backend is local-only (Ollama/Mock) -- nothing leaves the machine.
# Setting this key does NOT change that: DeepSeek is used only when you select it
# by name (--backend deepseek / --llm deepseek). With the key set and the backend
# chosen, prompts and generated speech are sent to api.deepseek.com.
#
# Privacy note: DeepSeek is China-hosted, retains inputs ~30 days, and its policy
# permits use for "model improvement". Turn off "Improve the model for everyone"
# in your account to keep prompts out of training. There is no real-person data
# in this sim, but the system prompts are your own (unpublished) prompt design.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
